# Project Purpose
The goal is to build a web app that logs when a button representing a chicken item (e.g. nuggets, filets, spicy filets) is pressed.
Each press logs the button type and timestamp to a Firebase backend.
Data must be accessible and exportable via Google Sheets.
This app will run on a single tablet and does not require authentication or multi-user support.

# Frontend Rules
- Use React with functional components and Tailwind CSS (or Shadcn UI if available).
- The UI should show a simple dashboard of labeled buttons (e.g. “Nuggets”, “Filets”, etc.).
- When a button is pressed:
  - Provide immediate feedback (e.g., flash the button or show “Logged” text).
  - Send the button name and current timestamp to the backend.
  - Doesn't allow the same button to be pressed until after a 1 min cooldown.
- Include a basic view that shows recent button presses.

# Backend Rules
- Use Firebase (Firestore) to store button press logs.
- Each log entry should contain:
  - `button_type`: string
  - `timestamp`: ISO 8601 string (e.g. "2025-07-15T18:34:00Z")
  - This will be in Hawaii Standard Time or GMT-10.
- No authentication or user IDs are needed.
- Firebase config should be in `.env` and not hardcoded.

# Google Sheets Integration
- Sync Firebase data to Google Sheets using a Firebase → Google Sheets automation (e.g. via Google Apps Script or Make/Zapier).
- Prefer appending new rows with fields: [timestamp, button_type].
- This export does not need to be triggered from the web app — it can be automatic in the background.

# Coding Style
- Keep all components clean, minimal, and self-contained.
- Use `async/await` and error handling for all Firebase writes.
- Use comments to explain all Firebase interactions.

# Colors and Theme
- Use the #E60E33 Red Color and White #FFFFFF
- Use round edges on each button and keep each button simple with just the following names, 
(Nuggets, Filets, Spicy Filets, Grilled Nuggets, Grilled Filets, Strips)

# Out of Scope
- No user authentication
- No advanced charting or analytics
- No mobile responsiveness optimization beyond basic tablet layout

# Goals
- Simplicity, clarity, and reliability
- Easy-to-understand code and UI for non-developers
- Exported log data must be clearly viewable in a spreadsheet

